ured by <em>xt</em>. This may include private insights, tacit domain knowle=
dge, internalized heuristics, and intuition.</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0=
;">Humans can access both observable and unobservable information. However,=
 they process this information imperfectly, which introduces an error term.=
 =E2=80=A6=C2=A0</p> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Algorithms, by contrast, =
can only access <em>xt</em>, but they process <em>xt</em> efficiently. =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0This represents traditional algorithmic forecasting using machi=
ne learning techniques. We, however, employ LLMs, which form expectations i=
n a nondeterministic manner.</p> </blockquote> <p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"=
